Second Lady Karen Pence visited the Tracy's Kids Art Therapy Program at MedStar Georgetown University Hospital in Washington, DC. She was greeted by several doctors and hospital staff members before observing an art therapy session with pediatric patients. Mrs. Pence also participated in a roundtable discussion with art therapists and hospital staff members. She has been a board member of Tracy's Kids since 2011 and was honored with the Courage Award in 2017 for her support of art therapy programs. Tracy's Kids uses art therapy to help young cancer patients and their families cope with the emotional stress of cancer and its treatment. The program is provided at no cost to the children and families at various clinics across the United States.